The paper deals with formal languages and their operations, which are topics in logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). It also involves the use of coinduction, which is a technique in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper specifically focuses on regular languages (cs.FL) and Kleene algebra (cs.LT), which are subfields of language theory.
